While a galactic outflow that expels preferentially metal-rich matter processed by massive stars is a convenient way of reducing the effective yield of a stellar population, the very low star formation rates observed in some metal-poor and extremely metal-poor dwarf galaxies would actually point to a mild outflow effect. In fact, star formation rates lower than 1M⊙yr-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
