The properties of local star-forming galaxies can be usefully compared to those of their higher-redshift counterparts, providing important clues on the evolution of the CNO elements, in particular the N/O ratio. Hayden-Pawson et al. (2022) compare the trends of log(N/O) as functions of metallicity and stellar mass emerging from a sample of 37 z∼\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
